-- ECB's Mersch: Buying state bonds, gold or shares 'theoretically' possible
-- 
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 04:10AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Nov 17 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank could theoretically buy state bonds or other assets such as gold, shares or exchange traded funds, ECB Executive Board member Yves Mersch said on Monday.

Commenting on the 'unconventional' options that were open to the central bank, Mersch said: "Theoretically, those could include the buying of state bonds or other assets such as gold, shares, exchange traded funds, etc."